1. Get 2 Pieces of Origami Paper and slice each down each corner leaving a little bit aat the center.
2. Glue the papers to each other with one paper as a diamond, and one as a square.
3. Fold in each corner to the center and glue to a small paper square to hold each end in place.
4. Run circuitry and place switch and batteries, along with the lights to make it light up
5. Solder the switch in place and soldker each led to the copper tape, don't rip the copper tape, only fold it.
6. Add magnet to the switch to turn it on, and there you go!
